00:05:17,080 --> 00:05:20,160
 that was unfamiliar and even risky.

118
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:23,480
 In the same way as a church family,

119
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:27,640
 we are navigating our own uncharted waters.

120
00:05:27,640 --> 00:05:30,000
 Maybe we're starting a new ministry,

121
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:31,400
 reaching out to new people,

122
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:35,360
 or simply learning to trust God in our journey.

123
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:39,160
 In situations where we feel uncertain or overwhelming,

124
00:05:39,160 --> 00:05:41,280
 just like the early disciples,

125
00:05:41,280 --> 00:05:43,840
 we might feel small, unprepared,

126
00:05:43,840 --> 00:05:46,880
 unsure of how to move forward.

127
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:50,400
 But the good news is we are not alone.

128
00:05:50,400 --> 00:05:53,440
 In the first week, our elder Deborah shared with us

129
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:57,320
 about what it means to wait in active faith.

