 sent from the battlefield.

269
00:11:51,640 --> 00:11:54,760
 Imagine a city full of anxious people

270
00:11:54,760 --> 00:11:57,560
 waiting to hear who had won the war.

271
00:11:57,560 --> 00:12:00,160
 And then the herald finally arrived

272
00:12:00,160 --> 00:12:01,840
 and shouted the good news,

273
00:12:01,840 --> 00:12:04,280
 the victory, to these people

274
00:12:04,280 --> 00:12:05,600
 and everything changed.

275
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:07,720
 The whole city rejoiced.

276
00:12:07,720 --> 00:12:10,240
 The future looked different.

277
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:12,040
 The Greek word for this word,

278
00:12:12,040 --> 00:12:13,200
 this joyful announcement,

279
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:16,240
 is called euangelion.

280
00:12:16,240 --> 00:12:18,240
 The same word we use for gospel

281
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:20,320
 or the good news.

282
00:12:20,320 --> 00:12:21,640
 This is the picture

283
00:12:21,640 --> 00:12:23,600
 that the first Christian used

284
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:26,160
 when they talked about Jesus.

285
00:12:26,160 --> 00:12:28,200
 They believed that through his death

286
00:12:28,200 --> 00:12:29,480
 and resurrection,

287
00:12:29,480 --> 00:12:31,320
 Jesus had already won

288
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:32,640
 the ultimate victory

289
00:12:32,640 --> 00:12:35,360
 over sin, death, and evil.

290
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:36,600
 The victory is real.

291
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:39,120
 It has already happened.

292
00:12:39,120 --> 00:12:40,480
 But just like history,

293
00:12:40,480 --> 00:12:42,400
 imagine World War II, right?

294
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:43,840
 For example,

295
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:45,920
 even after the enemy

296
00:12:45,920 --> 00:12:48,280
 was defeated in their homeland,

297
00:12:48,280 --> 00:12:51,720
 many places still lived under occupation.

298
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:54,200
 The news of the victory has arrived,

299
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:56,000
 but the effects hadn't reached

300
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:57,600
 every corner yet.

301
00:12:57,600 --> 00:12:59,200
 People in those places

302
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:01,320
 lived in the in-betweens.

303
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:03,320
 They knew victory was won,

304
00:13:03,320 --> 00:13:04,680
 but the old powers

305
00:13:04,680 --> 00:13:08,040
 were still in the present for a time.

306
00:13:08,040 --> 00:13:10,000
 And that's the world we live in.

307
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,520
 That's the world we live in.

308
00:13:11,520 --> 00:13:13,000
 We've heard the good news

309
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:15,080
 that Jesus has won,

310
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:18,120
 but we still live and experience pain,

311
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:21,280
 suffering, and injustice.

312
00:13:21,280 --> 00:13:23,080
 The effects of his victory

313
00:13:23,080 --> 00:13:25,120
 are not fully here yet.

314
00:13:25,120 --> 00:13:26,920
 We live in this tension,

315
00:13:26,920 --> 00:13:30,480
 this already but not yet tension.

316
00:13:30,480 --> 00:13:31,960
 So what does it mean

317
00:13:31,960 --> 00:13:34,200
 to be a witness in Christ?

318
00:13:34,200 --> 00:13:36,000
 It means being like the herald

319
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:38,320
 who brings the news of victory.

320
00:13:38,320 --> 00:13:40,760
 It means living, speaking,

321
00:13:40,760 --> 00:13:42,640
 and making choices in ways

322
00:13:42,640 --> 00:13:44,000
 that show people

323
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:45,920
 Jesus has already won.

324
00:13:45,920 --> 00:13:48,040
 Even while we wait for the fullness

325
00:13:48,040 --> 00:13:49,920
 of his victory to come,

326
00:13:49,920 --> 00:13:52,680
 our lives become signals to the world

327
00:13:52,680 --> 00:13:55,680
 that a new reality has begun.

328
00:13:55,680 --> 00:13:57,720
 Even in a world that hasn't yet seen

329
00:13:57,720 --> 00:13:59,680
 the final peace,

330
00:13:59,680 --> 00:14:01,240
 we live as a people

331
00:14:01,240 --> 00:14:04,960
 who know that the outcome is secure.

332
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:06,840
 And how can we do something

333
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:09,280
 that seems impossible?

334
00:14:09,280 --> 00:14:10,840
 That seems impossible, right?

335
00:14:10,840 --> 00:14:12,640
 We are living in this injustice.

336
00:14:12,640 --> 00:14:15,880
 We're experiencing pain and suffering,

337
00:14:15,880 --> 00:14:17,760
 and we have to show people that,

338
00:14:17,760 --> 00:14:20,080
 no, the victory is done.

339
00:14:20,080 --> 00:14:22,040
 We are set free from our sin.

340
00:14:22,040 --> 00:14:23,880
 We are set free from our pain.

341
00:14:23,880 --> 00:14:26,960
 There can be justice in this place,

342
00:14:26,960 --> 00:14:28,840
 but I don't see it yet.

343
00:14:28,840 --> 00:14:30,560
 Nor my friends have seen it yet,

344
00:14:30,560 --> 00:14:32,440
 but I have to live and speak

345
00:14:32,440 --> 00:14:34,360
 and make decisions and choose

346
00:14:34,360 --> 00:14:37,400
 as if the final victory

347
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:39,480
 is here already.

348
00:14:39,480 --> 00:14:41,640
 How can we do something

349
00:14:41,640 --> 00:14:44,800
 that seems near impossible?

350
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:47,040
 But before the commission,

351
00:14:47,040 --> 00:14:50,080
 there was the promise.

352
00:14:50,080 --> 00:14:52,000
 You will receive power

353
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:54,280
 when the Holy Spirit comes on you.

354
00:14:54,280 --> 00:14:56,640
 You will receive power.

355
00:14:56,640 --> 00:14:59,080
 We are empowered by the Holy Spirit

356
00:14:59,080 --> 00:15:00,680
 to live out this command.

357
00:15:00,680 --> 00:15:01,800
 We're not doing this

358
00:15:01,800 --> 00:15:03,320
 out of our own strength,

359
00:15:03,320 --> 00:15:05,240
 nor we should be.

360
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:07,520
 We have access to the Holy Spirit,

361
00:15:07,520 --> 00:15:10,040
 who is our ever-present help.

362
00:15:10,040 --> 00:15:13,000
 We are empowered.

363
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:15,040
 Peter's life and his sermon

364
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:17,360
 after Pentecost is a demonstration

365
00:15:17,360 --> 00:15:19,800
 of how the Spirit empowers us

366
00:15:19,800 --> 00:15:21,520
 for this mission.

367
00:15:21,520 --> 00:15:22,800
 Just look at, can you recall

368
00:15:22,800 --> 00:15:25,200
 some of what Peter has gone through

369
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:26,280
 before the Pentecost,

370
00:15:26,280 --> 00:15:27,960
 before Jesus died?

371
00:15:27,960 --> 00:15:29,480
 He boldly walked on water

372
00:15:29,480 --> 00:15:30,560
 for a moment,

373
00:15:30,560 --> 00:15:32,280
 and then sank in fear.

374
00:15:32,280 --> 00:15:34,360
 He tried to defend Jesus

375
00:15:34,360 --> 00:15:36,320
 by cutting off soldiers' ear,

376
00:15:36,320 --> 00:15:38,160
 acting impulsively.

377
00:15:38,160 --> 00:15:39,800
 Most painfully,

378
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:41,960
 he denied even knowing Jesus

379
00:15:41,960 --> 00:15:43,800
 three times.

380
00:15:43,800 --> 00:15:45,880
 In all of these moments,

381
00:15:45,880 --> 00:15:48,040
 Peter's action was driven

382
00:15:48,040 --> 00:15:49,160
 by what you called

383
00:15:49,160 --> 00:15:52,800
 self-reliance zeal.

384
00:15:52,800 --> 00:15:55,480
 This means that he was relying

385
00:15:55,480 --> 00:15:57,800
 mostly on his own energy,

386
00:15:57,800 --> 00:16:00,360
 his own ideas of what should be done,

387
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:01,800
 and his own desire

388
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:04,640
 to prove his loyalty to Jesus.

389
00:16:04,640 --> 00:16:06,920
 It was courage fueled

390
00:16:06,920 --> 00:16:08,720
 by his own effort,

391
00:16:08,720 --> 00:16:10,080
 by trying harder,

392
00:16:10,080 --> 00:16:11,240
 by pushing forward,

393
00:16:11,240 --> 00:16:13,840
 by reacting in the moment.

394
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:16,600
 But no matter how sincere he was,

395
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:18,000
 it wasn't enough.

396
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:20,240
 His courage kept running out

397
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:22,640
 when the pressure was on.

398
00:16:22,640 --> 00:16:24,320
 Peter was passionate.

399
00:16:24,320 --> 00:16:26,160
 He wanted to be faithful,

400
00:16:26,160 --> 00:16:28,440
 but over and over again,

401
00:16:28,440 --> 00:16:30,760
 he found himself falling short,

402
00:16:30,760 --> 00:16:32,840
 sinking, falling,

403
00:16:32,840 --> 00:16:35,480
 acting out of fear or confusion.

404
00:16:35,480 --> 00:16:37,480
 He was just like us,

405
00:16:37,480 --> 00:16:39,320
 full of good intention,

406
00:16:39,320 --> 00:16:41,320
 but often lacking the strength

407
00:16:41,320 --> 00:16:44,040
 to follow through.

408
00:16:44,040 --> 00:16:46,120
 Don't know if you've ever felt that way.

409
00:16:46,120 --> 00:16:47,880
 We wanted to do something good

410
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:50,160
 for people, to serve them,

411
00:16:50,160 --> 00:16:51,800
 but accidentally,

412
00:16:51,800 --> 00:16:54,200
 not of our own choosing.

413
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:56,960
 We hurt them by forcing our thoughts

414
00:16:56,960 --> 00:16:58,440
 and ideas over them,

415
00:16:58,440 --> 00:17:00,640
 by questioning them too hard.

416
00:17:00,640 --> 00:17:02,720
 That was absolutely me.

417
00:17:02,720 --> 00:17:03,880
 When I was younger,

418
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:05,400
 in my university year,

419
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:09,040
 I had a friend who is like Eeyore

420
00:17:09,040 --> 00:17:11,880
 in Winnie the Pooh.

421
00:17:11,880 --> 00:17:13,040
 I know, I know.

422
00:17:13,040 --> 00:17:15,000
 I feel so sorry for him too.

423
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:16,480
 Like, he is a Christian.

424
00:17:16,480 --> 00:17:17,760
 We have been together in the church

425
00:17:17,760 --> 00:17:18,960
 for many years,

426
00:17:18,960 --> 00:17:20,160
 and he would come and say,

427
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:22,480
 "Hi."

428
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:23,800
 And I go,

429
00:17:23,800 --> 00:17:24,520
 "What do you like?

430
00:17:24,520 --> 00:17:26,600
 You know, you don't have to."

431
00:17:26,600 --> 00:17:28,520
 Also, he served in church a lot.

432
00:17:28,520 --> 00:17:30,840
 He is in the production team.

433
00:17:30,840 --> 00:17:32,520
 He also lead worship.

434
00:17:32,520 --> 00:17:34,200
 He also do a lot of stuff,

435
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:36,000
 but he just felt so broken

436
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:37,960
 and so tired all the time,

437
00:17:37,960 --> 00:17:40,400
 and nothing brings him joy.

438
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:42,120
 In my heart, I really want him

439
00:17:42,120 --> 00:17:43,520
 to be joyful.

440
00:17:43,520 --> 00:17:45,040
 I believe that as you're a Christian,

441
00:17:45,040 --> 00:17:45,760
 you should be,

442
00:17:45,760 --> 00:17:47,160
 you can be joyful.

443
00:17:47,160 --> 00:17:48,360
 This is the life that Jesus

444
00:17:48,360 --> 00:17:50,280
 has given to us.

445
00:17:50,280 --> 00:17:51,960
 That was my intention.

446
00:17:51,960 --> 00:17:53,560
 But at the end of the day,

447
00:17:53,560 --> 00:17:55,440
 he go, "June, can you not ask me

448
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:56,680
 any more questions?

449
00:17:56,680 --> 00:17:58,080
 Can you just stay away from me

450
00:17:58,080 --> 00:17:58,760
 for a while?

451
00:17:58,760 --> 00:18:01,440
 You are pushing me too hard."

452
00:18:01,440 --> 00:18:03,880
 And I realized that no matter

453
00:18:03,880 --> 00:18:05,760
 how good my intention is,

454
00:18:05,760 --> 00:18:07,280
 I was hurting him.

455
00:18:07,280 --> 00:18:08,800
 I was pushing my idea

456
00:18:08,800 --> 00:18:10,840
 of what a Christian look like

457
00:18:10,840 --> 00:18:12,760
 onto him.

458
00:18:12,760 --> 00:18:14,160
 It was good intention,

459
00:18:15,160 --> 00:18:17,760
 but falling short.

460
00:18:17,760 --> 00:18:20,000
 But then we see Peter

461
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:21,400
 after Pentecost.

462
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:23,640
 In Acts 2.25,

463
00:18:23,640 --> 00:18:25,640
 we see that Peter was not alone.

464
00:18:25,640 --> 00:18:28,320
 He was filled with the Holy Spirit.

465
00:18:28,320 --> 00:18:29,560
 Peter stands in front

466
00:18:29,560 --> 00:18:30,800
 of a huge crowd

467
00:18:30,800 --> 00:18:33,240
 and preached by citing Psalm 16.

468
00:18:33,240 --> 00:18:34,040
 He says,

469
00:18:34,040 --> 00:18:35,600
 "David said about him,

470
00:18:35,600 --> 00:18:37,800
 'I saw the Lord was always

471
00:18:37,800 --> 00:18:38,720
 before me,

472
00:18:38,720 --> 00:18:40,920
 because he is at my right hand.

473
00:18:40,920 --> 00:18:42,680
 I will not be shaken.

474
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:44,160
 Therefore, my heart is glad

475
00:18:44,160 --> 00:18:45,440
 and my tongue rejoices.

476
00:18:45,440 --> 00:18:47,560
 My body will also rest in hope,

477
00:18:47,560 --> 00:18:49,200
 because you will not abandon me

478
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:50,760
 to the realm of the dead.

479
00:18:50,760 --> 00:18:52,640
 You will not let your Holy One

480
00:18:52,640 --> 00:18:54,320
 see decay.'"

481
00:18:54,320 --> 00:18:56,640
 Here is what Peter is doing.

482
00:18:56,640 --> 00:18:58,840
 He's looking back at what

483
00:18:58,840 --> 00:19:00,600
 King David wrote in the Psalms,

484
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:02,280
 and he realized David

485
00:19:02,280 --> 00:19:04,920
 wasn't just talking about himself.

486
00:19:04,920 --> 00:19:07,160
 David was pointing forward

487
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:09,080
 to someone greater,

488
00:19:09,080 --> 00:19:10,920
 the true Holy One,

489
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:12,440
 who would not stay dead,

490
00:19:12,440 --> 00:19:14,280
 who would rise again.

491
00:19:14,280 --> 00:19:16,160
 Peter saw that Jesus

492
00:19:16,160 --> 00:19:18,560
 is the only one that truly fits

493
00:19:18,560 --> 00:19:20,920
 what David describes.

494
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:22,880
 Jesus is the Holy One

495
00:19:22,880 --> 00:19:25,640
 who died but did not see decay,

496
00:19:25,640 --> 00:19:27,240
 because God raised him

497
00:19:27,240 --> 00:19:28,960
 from the dead.

498
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:30,600
 Peter's sermon at Pentecost

499
00:19:30,600 --> 00:19:32,240
 wasn't about condemning

500
00:19:32,240 --> 00:19:33,680
 or passing judgment,

501
00:19:33,680 --> 00:19:34,680
 telling them off that,

502
00:19:34,680 --> 00:19:35,520
 "You should have known

503
00:19:35,520 --> 00:19:37,120
 the Bible said so clearly."

504
00:19:37,120 --> 00:19:38,480
 He wasn't judging them

505
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:39,960
 for not knowing.

506
00:19:39,960 --> 00:19:42,680
 No, Peter was one of them.

507
00:19:42,680 --> 00:19:45,080
 He was a Jew who had grown up

508
00:19:45,080 --> 00:19:46,240
 with the same hopes

509
00:19:46,240 --> 00:19:47,600
 and same dreams,

510
00:19:47,600 --> 00:19:49,000
 waiting for God's promise

511
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:50,960
 to be fulfilled.

512
00:19:50,960 --> 00:19:52,520
 Just like everyone who listens

513
00:19:52,520 --> 00:19:53,760
 to him that day,

514
00:19:53,760 --> 00:19:55,320
 Peter had wondered,

515
00:19:55,320 --> 00:19:57,720
 "When will the Messiah come?

516
00:19:57,720 --> 00:19:59,240
 Who is going to fulfill

517
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:00,640
 all that God promised

518
00:20:00,640 --> 00:20:02,120
 to King David?"

519
00:20:02,120 --> 00:20:03,480
 His heart was full

520
00:20:03,480 --> 00:20:05,240
 of the same longing,

521
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:06,760
 the same question

522
00:20:06,760 --> 00:20:09,480
 as the people gathered around him.

523
00:20:09,480 --> 00:20:10,680
 But now,

524
00:20:10,680 --> 00:20:12,960
 filled with the Holy Spirit,

525
00:20:12,960 --> 00:20:14,680
 Peter boldly announces

526
00:20:14,680 --> 00:20:16,480
 that the answer to those hopes

527
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:19,240
 and those dreams is Jesus,

528
00:20:19,240 --> 00:20:20,000
 the Son of God,

529
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:21,760
 the true descendant of David,

530
00:20:21,760 --> 00:20:24,560
 and the long-awaited Messiah.

531
00:20:24,560 --> 00:20:25,720
 Peter's message

532
00:20:25,720 --> 00:20:28,120
 was deeply personal.

533
00:20:28,120 --> 00:20:29,640
 He wasn't delivering

534
00:20:29,640 --> 00:20:31,560
 cold theology.

535
00:20:31,560 --> 00:20:32,920
 He was sharing

536
00:20:32,920 --> 00:20:33,720
 the fulfillment

537
00:20:33,720 --> 00:20:36,840
 of his people's greatest hope.

538
00:20:36,840 --> 00:20:39,720
 He stood not as an outsider,

539
00:20:39,720 --> 00:20:41,280
 but a fellow seeker

540
00:20:41,280 --> 00:20:43,360
 whose eyes had been opened

541
00:20:43,360 --> 00:20:46,160
 by God's grace.

542
00:20:46,160 --> 00:20:46,960
 This is what it means

543
00:20:46,960 --> 00:20:48,480
 to be a witness.

544
00:20:48,480 --> 00:20:49,600
 To be a witness

545
00:20:49,600 --> 00:20:52,080
 is not simply to declare facts

546
00:20:52,080 --> 00:20:54,360
 or argue people into believing.

547
00:20:54,360 --> 00:20:56,160
 It is much more than that.

548
00:20:56,160 --> 00:20:57,360
 Being a witness,

549
00:20:57,360 --> 00:20:58,680
 as Peter shows us,

550
00:20:58,680 --> 00:21:00,640
 means stepping into the world

551
00:21:00,640 --> 00:21:02,680
 of the people we are speaking to,

552
00:21:02,680 --> 00:21:04,240
 understanding their fears,

553
00:21:04,240 --> 00:21:05,200
 their hopes,

554
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:07,440
 and their deepest question.

555
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:08,640
 It means that allowing

556
00:21:08,640 --> 00:21:10,520
 the Holy Spirit to fill us

557
00:21:10,520 --> 00:21:12,280
 so that our words come out

558
00:21:12,280 --> 00:21:15,200
 not from pride or distance,

559
00:21:15,200 --> 00:21:17,320
 but from genuine compassion

560
00:21:17,320 --> 00:21:20,080
 and shared humanity.

561
00:21:20,080 --> 00:21:21,280
 For us today,

562
00:21:21,280 --> 00:21:22,720
 being witness of Jesus

563
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:25,680
 is more than just sharing a message.

